Here is an example of a C# provider pattern for connecting to Elasticsearch and Redis:


```
interface IDataProvider
{
 void Connect();
 void Disconnect();
}

class ElasticsearchProvider : IDataProvider
{
 private ElasticClient _client;

 public void Connect()
 {
 var connectionSettings = new ConnectionSettings(new Uri("http://localhost:9200"))
 .DefaultIndex("myindex");
 _client = new ElasticClient(connectionSettings);
 }

 public void Disconnect()
 {
 _client = null;
 }
}

class RedisProvider : IDataProvider
{
 private ConnectionMultiplexer _redis;

 public void Connect()
 {
 _redis = ConnectionMultiplexer.Connect("localhost");
 }

 public void Disconnect()
 {
 _redis.Close();
 }
}
```
This is a basic example, you can customize it according to your requirements.

In this example, the `ElasticsearchProvider` class connects to Elasticsearch using the `ElasticClient` class from the Elasticsearch.Net library and the `RedisProvider` class connects to Redis using the `ConnectionMultiplexer` class from the StackExchange.Redis library.

Both classes implement the `IDataProvider` interface, which defines a `Connect` and `Disconnect` method.

You can now use the providers like this:


```
IDataProvider provider = new ElasticsearchProvider();
provider.Connect();

// Do something with Elasticsearch

provider.Disconnect();
```
Note that, you need to have the nuget packages installed for Elasticsearch.Net and StackExchange.Redis to work.

